It took just one moment of magic, one goal in his first training session as a Manchester United player, for Louis van Gaal to appreciate that Radamel Falcao could be an awful lot of money well spent.

‘When you can hire or buy a player like Falcao then I don’t have doubts because he is, for me, one of the best strikers in the world. When you see his record it is unbelievable,’ said Van Gaal at a press conference to unveil the 28-year-old Colombia striker.

‘At training he got one ball and it was in the goal. He confirmed it in his first training session with me. But when I say that, I put too much pressure on him and that’s not good.’ 

