United’s new signing spoke mainly in broken English but answered a couple of questions from the South American media more fluently in Spanish.

As he got up to leave at the end, Van Gaal grabbed him by the right arm and addressed his audience.

‘What do you think about his English?’ asked the former Barcelona coach. ‘Because I had the same situation in Spain. In my first year I spoke English, in my second year Spanish. And he is coming here and he is speaking English for you. Yeah, OK?’

It brought a round of applause but, for this kind of money, United supporters will expect Radamel Falcao to do his talking on the pitch.

